org.epics.pvData.misc
Interface LinkedListArray<T>

public interface LinkedListArray<T>

Convert a LinkedList to a LinkedListNode array. LinkedListCreate provides an efficient implementation.

Author:
mrk

Method Summary

          Clear the array.

Method Detail

setNodes

void setNodes(LinkedList<T> linkedList)
Set the LinkNode array from linkedList. If the current capacity of the array is less than the number of elements in the current array a new array is allocated. The values returned by getNodes and getLength are determined by the argument passed to setNodes. The linkedList is traversed by getHead and getNext.

Parameters:
linkedList - The list.

getNodes

LinkedListNode<T>[] getNodes()
The LinkedListNode array as set by the last call to setNodes.

Returns:
The LinkedListNode array. The first getLength() elements are not null and the remaining elements are all null.

getLength

int getLength()
The number of non-null elements in the array returned by getNodes.

Returns:
the length.

clear

void clear()
Clear the array. The array is set to null.
